## Life is a quality that describes matter which has self-sustaining and self-replicating properties 

- Individual life-forms are known as **organisms**

- All life-forms...
	- ...contain and are based on genetic material...
		- ...primarily as DNA, but also RNA
		- Are capable of mutation and [[Unsorted/Biodiversity\|genetic variation]]
	- ...are able to reproduce
	- ...self-regulate to achieve homeostasis
	- ...have a [[Metabolism\|metabolism]]
		- [[Unsorted/Respiration\|Respiration]], creation of structural/functional compounds, and eliminating waste 
		- ...to perform biological functions
	- ...are capable of growth...
		- ...typically including self-repair
	- ~~...respond to environmental stimuli~~

- Includes [[Unsorted/Viruses\|Viruses]] to *some* extent, because they have genetic material, undergo mutations, and evolve

## Prokaryotes
### Archaea
- Ancient
- Extremophiles
	- Thermophiles
	- Halophiles (salt-loving)
- Methanogens
	- Cow digestive system and swamps

### [[Bacteria\|Bacteria]]
- Very numerous, ubiquitous
- Can be beneficial, harmful, or benign
- Vital for all complex life
- [[Unsorted/Biodiversity\|Horizontal Gene Transfer]]

### [[Unsorted/Viruses\|Viruses]]

- Cannot reproduce on their own
	- Almost always lack the cellular machinery required for genetic duplication and protein creation
	- They use the machinery of other lifeforms
- While not typically considered alive


## Eukaryotes
- Organisms whose cells contain [[Unsorted/Endosymbiotes\|endosymbiotic]] organisms known as [[Unsorted/Endosymbiotes\|Mitochondria]], which drastically improve the efficiency of respiration

### Protists
- Amoebas
- Slime molds
- Algae

###### Dawn of multicellular life

### [[Unsorted/Fungi\|Fungi]]

	- Essential to nutrient cycles
- Very frequently act as [[Unsorted/Communities\|Symbiotes]] to other organisms
	- [[Unsorted/Fungi\|Fungi]]
	- Lichens
		- Fungi with [[Unsorted/Endosymbiotes\|endosymbiotic]] algae

## Energy sources
- All organisms require energy to survive and function
	- Organisms need an energy source, or they will gradually be destroyed by entropy 
- There are two types:


### Autotrophs
- Get their energy from an abiotic source
- Two subtypes
	- [[Unsorted/Photosynthesis\|Photoautotrophs]]
		- Produce energy from the sun's light
		- Primary source of the majority of energy used by all [[Unsorted/Life\|Life]] on [[Unsorted/Earth\|Earth]] 
	- Chemoautotrophs
		- Produce energy from chemicals in their environment


### Heterotrophs
- Get their energy from a biotic source via [[Unsorted/Respiration\|Respiration]]
	- Consuming other organisms
	- Consuming biological detritus
	- [[Unsorted/Communities\|Symbiosis]] with autotrophs
		- [[Unsorted/Fungi\|Fungi]]
		- Hosts of [[Unsorted/Endosymbiotes\|Endosymbiotes]]
- Subtypes:
	- Herbivores
		- Organisms that consume living plants
	- Carnivores
		- Organisms that consume living animals
	- Detritivores
		- Organisms that consume dead organic material
		- Such as fungi, many prokaryotes, carrion animals

### Exceptions
- A species of sea slug that can photosynthesize
	- Elysia chlorotica
	- Lyses algal membranes, and digests everything except the chloroplasts
		- Keep the algal chloroplasts inside of them, not algal [[Unsorted/Endosymbiotes\|Endosymbiotes]]
		- Does not need to eat again once it has enough
	- It even has genes to synthesize its own chlorophyll
